## The Assembly CTW Illusion

This is the most common source of buyer disappointment in cluster and halo drop earring purchases, and most buyers never hear about it until after they've already placed an order.

When Blue Nile lists a drop earring at "3 1/2 Ct. Tw." or "4 Ct. Tw.", that number represents every stone in the entire assembly across both earrings. That means pear center stones, halo accent diamonds, marquise cluster stones, and melee are all added together to generate the headline CTW figure.

Here is why that matters in real terms: a pair listed at 3.5 CTW might contain 12 pear diamonds, 8 marquise stones, and 40 melee accent diamonds spread across both earrings. The pear center per ear could be 0.20–0.35 CTW. The individual pear stones are not large — the total weight is impressive but it is distributed across dozens of stones in a decorative composition.

This is completely different from how buyers read CTW in stud earrings. With studs, "1 CTW" tells you exactly what you're getting: 0.50 ct per ear, one stone each side. With cluster drops, the CTW tells you almost nothing about individual stone size.

| Listing | Stated CTW | Design | Est. Pear Per Ear |
|---|---|---|---|
| Lab Pear Halo Dangle | 2 CTW | 1 pear center + halo per ear | ~0.55–0.65 CTW |
| Pear+Marquise Leaf Cluster | 3.5 CTW | Multi-stone pear + marquise composition | ~0.25–0.35 CTW pear |
| Pear+Marquise Array Drop | 4 CTW | Array of pear + marquise | ~0.25–0.35 CTW pear |
| Trio Graduating Pear Drop | 2 CTW | 3 graduating pears per ear | ~0.30–0.40 CTW each |
| Diamond Trio Drop | 4 CTW | 3 large pears per ear | ~0.60–0.70 CTW each |

The rule: if you want the pear stone to be the identifiable visual centrepiece of the earring, look for listings labelled "Pear Shape Diamond Drop" or "Pear Shaped Lab-Grown Diamond Drop." Those have the pear as the primary stone. Anything with "Cluster," "Floral," or "Leaf" in the title uses pear as one element in a multi-stone composition.

